o distant future\", \"from\": 364, \"to\": 390}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 27-year-old fell narrowly short of reaching the men's 71kg gold medal match after being beaten on split decision by Mexico's Marco Verde in the semi-final at Roland Garros on Tuesday.\", \"from\": 394, \"to\": 581, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 514, \"end\": 520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999951775010099, \"rank\": 4.820834758585197e-06, \"text\": \"Mexico\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the men's 71kg gold medal match\", \"from\": 442, \"to\": 473}, {\"ngram\": \"split decision\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 510}, {\"ngram\": \"Roland Garros\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 569}, {\"ngram\": \"Tuesday\", \"from\": 573, \"to\": 580}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bronze means Richardson is the only British boxer at Paris 2024 to win a medal.\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 662, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 596, \"end\": 606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999999984925125, \"rank\": 1.5073981359221282e-09, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 619, \"end\": 626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9999999953734005, \"rank\": 4.494429123552947e-09, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}, {\"begin\": 636, \"end\": 646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.370153155243052e-19, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bronze\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 589}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 661}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was already guaranteed bronze following victory against Zeyad Eashash in the quarter-finals on Saturday and reflected on a bittersweet feeling after missing the chance to go for gold.\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 849, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 695}, {\"ngram\": \"victory\", \"from\": 706, \"to\": 713}, {\"ngram\": \"Zeyad Eashash\", \"from\": 722, \"to\": 735}, {\"ngram\": \"the quarter-finals\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 757}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 769}, {\"ngram\": \"a bittersweet feeling\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 808}, {\"ngram\": \"the chance\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 833}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 844, \"to\": 848}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said: \\\"It's very raw and it is hard to process right now.\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 911, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have won that bronze medal, but it's hard to fully celebrate because you are moving onto the next one and looking to change the colour of that medal.\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 1063, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that bronze medal\", \"from\": 923, \"to\": 940}, {\"ngram\": \"the colour\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1048}, {\"ngram\": \"that medal\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1062}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am sure I am going to make a conscious effort whenever the time's right - and hopefully sooner rather than later - to flick that switch and be proud of what I have achieved.\", \"from\": 1065, \"to\": 1241, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a conscious effort\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1113}, {\"ngram\": \"that switch\", \"from\": 1192, \"to\": 1203}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Because rightly or wrongly, I am the only British boxer to medal at these Games and I hope I have made the country proud.\\\"\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1366, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1286, \"end\": 1293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9999999953734005, \"rank\": 4.494429123552947e-09, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1323}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1358}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year Keely Hodgkinson reveals Grand Slam Track decision and 2025 ambitions Incredible days out and trips for autumn and winter Richardson started the semi-final well, landing a solid punch to Verde's face, but the Mexican grew back into the round throwing a series of different combinations and breaking through the British fighter's defence.\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1499, \"end\": 1515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 1623, \"end\": 1633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999999984925125, \"rank\": 1.5073981359221282e-09, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 1710, \"end\": 1717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\", \"score\": 0.5580509032060591, \"rank\": 0.6448244124092701, \"text\": \"Mexican\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\"}, {\"begin\": 1812, \"end\": 1819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9999999953734005, \"rank\": 4.494429123552947e-09, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Proud\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1413}, {\"ngram\": \"Enhanced Games Sports quiz\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1446}, {\"ngram\": \"100 hard questions\", \"from\": 1456, \"to\": 1474}, {\"ngram\": \"an incredible year\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1496}, {\"ngram\": \"Grand Slam Track decision\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1547}, {\"ngram\": \"2025 ambitions\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1566}, {\"ngram\": \"trips\", \"from\": 1591, \"to\": 1596}, {\"ngram\": \"autumn\", \"from\": 1601, \"to\": 1607}, {\"ngram\": \"the semi-final well\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1657}, {\"ngram\": \"a solid punch\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1680}, {\"ngram\": \"Verde's face\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1696}, {\"ngram\": \"the round\", \"from\": 1729, \"to\": 1738}, {\"ngram\": \"a series\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1756}, {\"ngram\": \"different combinations\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1782}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The second round saw the British fighter show off his skills, landing a great uppercut and a couple of big blows to Verde's head to take the round on the majority of the judges' cards.\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 2024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1865, \"end\": 1872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9999999953734005, \"rank\": 4.494429123552947e-09, \"text\": \"British\", \"t